Joey Logano celebrates in Victory Lane after winning the NASCAR Sprint Cup race at Charlotte Motor Speedway in Concord, N.C., Sunday, Oct. 11, 2015. Terry Renna Logano races into 3rd round of playoffs with Charlotte win 
Joey Logano celebrates in Victory Lane after winning the NASCAR Sprint Cup series auto race at Charlotte Motor Speedway in Concord, N.C., Sunday, Oct. 11, 2015. (AP Photo/Terry Renna) Chuck Burton Logano races into 3rd round of playoffs with Charlotte win 
Matt Kenseth walks to his truck after leaving the race during the NASCAR Sprint Cup series auto race at Charlotte Motor Speedway in Concord, N.C., Sunday, Oct. 11, 2015. (AP Photo/Chuck Burton) Chuck Burton Logano races into 3rd round of playoffs with Charlotte win 
Jimmie Johnson leaves his car in the garage during the NASCAR Sprint Cup series auto race at Charlotte Motor Speedway in Concord, N.C., Sunday, Oct. 11, 2015. (AP Photo/Chuck Burton) David Graham Logano races into 3rd round of playoffs with Charlotte win 
Kyle Busch (18) hits Kyle Larson (42) at the entrance to pit road during the NASCAR Sprint Cup series auto race at Charlotte Motor Speedway in Concord, N.C., Sunday, Oct. 11, 2015. (AP Photo/David Graham) Posted: Sunday, October 11, 2015 6:11 pm Logano races into 3rd round of playoffs with Charlotte win Associated Press | 
CONCORD — Joey Logano has been to victory lane four times this season, and all four trips required him to beat reigning Sprint Cup champion Kevin Harvick. 
The latest win, Sunday at Charlotte Motor Speedway, was a critical and confidence-building victory. He again shrugged off Harvick to earn an automatic berth into the third round of the Chase for the Sprint Cup championship.
